.TH "__unregister_chrdev" 9 "__unregister_chrdev" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
__unregister_chrdev \- unregister and destroy a cdev
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" __unregister_chrdev
.BI "(unsigned int major "  ","
.BI "unsigned int baseminor "  ","
.BI "unsigned int count "  ","
.BI "const char *name "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "major" 12
major device number
.IP "baseminor" 12
first of the range of minor numbers
.IP "count" 12
the number of minor numbers this cdev is occupying
.IP "name" 12
name of this range of devices
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Unregister and destroy the cdev occupying the region described by
\fImajor\fP, \fIbaseminor\fP and \fIcount\fP.  This function undoes what
\fB__register_chrdev\fP did.
